Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@yellow onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Drain and rinse
@kidney beans{1}. Reserve ½ tsp @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon} in
a #small bowl{}. Halve @brioche buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Place half the beans in a #large bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or fork
until mostly smooth (it's OK if there are still some larger pieces).

Stir in minced onion, ¾ of the @tempura mix{82%g}(reserve some for batter), half
the @pepper jack cheese{½%cup}, remaining BBQ seasoning, and 3 TBSP water until
thoroughly combined. Season with @salt{¼%tsp} and @pepper{}.

Divide bean mixture into two mounds. Set aside.

> All for 4 servings - place half the beans and reserve some for the second batch.

== BBQ Caramelized Onion ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large, preferably nonstick, pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and season with @salt{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in half the @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}; cook until warmed through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; transfer onion to a second small bowl. Carefully wash
out pan.

== BBQ Mayo ==

While onion cooks, to bowl with reserved BBQ seasoning, stir in
@mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, 1 tsp pickle brine, and @sugar{¼%teaspoon}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Bean Burgers ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for onion over medium-high heat.
Using a #rubber spatula{}, add bean mixture mounds to pan and gently press to
flatten into patties, each about as wide as a burger bun. Cook until bottoms are
golden brown and crisp, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Flip patties and carefully top with remaining pepper jack. Cover with a #lid{}
and cook until bottoms are crisp and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Transfer
to a #plate{}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches, adding
> another drizzle of oil between batches.

== Assembly ==

While patties cook, toast buns until golden; spread cut sides of top buns with
remaining BBQ sauce. Spread cut sides of bottom buns with half the BBQ mayo.

Fill buns with patties, onion, and as many @dill pickle slices{1}(sliced) as you
like.

Divide burgers between plates. Serve with potato wedges, any remaining pickles,
and remaining BBQ mayo on the side for dipping.